            "sub_heading": "",
            "heading": "Cotton Saree Maintenance 101: No More Wrinkles or Fading!",
            "text": "<p>Cotton sarees are every desi girl’s best friend—lightweight, breathable, effortlessly elegant, and perfect for everything from morning meetings to lazy brunches. But if you've ever faced stiff wrinkles, dull colors, or fabric fatigue after just a few wears, you’re not alone.</p><p>Here's your <strong>ultimate guide to cotton saree maintenance</strong>—no more wrinkles, no more fading, just fresh, flawless drapes every time!</p><h2>Why Cotton Needs Extra TLC</h2><p>Cotton is a natural, absorbent fabric. It breathes beautifully but also tends to:</p><ul><li><strong>Wrinkle easily<br/><br/></strong></li><li><strong>Lose color over multiple washes<br/><br/></strong></li><li><strong>Stiffen or shrink if not stored properly</strong></li></ul><p>That’s why cotton sarees need gentle love, not harsh chemicals or careless storage.</p>",
