            "text_size": "40,15",
            "txt_align": "start",
            "sub_heading": "",
            "heading": "",
            "text": "<h2>Step-by-Step: How to Wash Cotton Sarees<br/><br/></h2><h4>1. First Wash = Cold Wash</h4><p>Always hand-wash your new cotton saree separately in <strong>cold water</strong> to avoid color bleeding.</p><h4>2. Use Mild Detergents</h4><p>Choose <strong>gentle, liquid detergents</strong> meant for delicate fabrics. Harsh powders cause fiber wear and fading.</p><h4>3. Avoid Soaking for Too Long</h4><p>A quick 5–10 minute soak is enough. Over-soaking leads to color bleeding and dullness.</p><h4>4. Skip the Wringing</h4><p>Never twist or wring your cotton saree. Gently squeeze out excess water and hang to dry in the shade.</p>",
