    "image_text_c8UhLh": {
      "type": "image_text",
      "blocks": {
        "bl_text_QTLBpH": {
          "type": "bl_text",
          "settings": {
            "col_dk": "12",
            "col_tb": "12",
            "text_size": "40,15",
            "txt_align": "start",
            "sub_heading": "",
            "heading": "",
            "text": "<h2>How to Dry Cotton Sarees Without Fading</h2><p>The sun is cotton’s frenemy. It dries the fabric fast but also bleaches the color.</p><ul><li><strong>Dry in shade only</strong>—preferably on a hanger or flat on a cotton towel<br/><br/></li><li><strong>Avoid clothespins on borders or pallu</strong>—they leave creases or stretch marks</li></ul><h2>How to Prevent Wrinkles in Cotton Sarees</h2><p>Wrinkles are cotton’s trademark—but you can manage them smartly!</p><ul><li><strong>When slightly damp,</strong> or use a steam iron<br/><br/></li><li><strong>Fold immediately after ironing</strong> to retain crispness<br/><br/></li><li><strong>Use starch if you like structure</strong> (but don’t overdo it!)</li></ul><p><strong>Bonus Tip:</strong> Keep a few lavender or neem sachets in your wardrobe to keep the fabric fresh and pest-free.</p>",
            "subhd_color": "#222222",
            "hd_color": "#222222",
            "des_color": "#878787",
            "use_shadow": false,
            "button_label": "Button label",
            "button_link": "",
